Description:
   Harbor Dust is an advanced Pugilist technique derived from dockside
   brawling traditions. The fighter reaches into a concealed pouch and hurls
   a mixture of fine abrasive dust directly into the opponent's face.
   The dust blinds and disorients the target, temporarily reducing their
   accuracy and ability to dodge.

   The technique requires no special tool — experienced Pugilists always
   carry a supply of the mixture. The dust cloud briefly surrounds the
   target's head, causing eye irritation and disorientation. While it deals
   no direct damage, the debilitating effect often turns the tide of a close
   fight by creating an opening for the Pugilist to deliver decisive blows.
   The effect is short-lived as most opponents can clear their eyes quickly.
